<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-524-103  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 524 103.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Oct 15 1990 v24 n42 p140(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software AG branches out. (Software AG of North America Inc.'sEntire plan)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ambrosio, Johanna.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Software AG of North America Inc is broadening its productdevelopment into programs for distributed and cooperativeprocessing.andP;  The overall plan, known as Entire, is a major changefor Software AG, which focuses normally on mainframe software.andO;The products Software AG plans to develop are designed to helpusers write applications for processing in multivendor computingenvironments.andP;  The first step is a series of programs under theumbrella 'Entire Function Server Technology.' Applicationsprogrammers can use these products to write applications in eitherCOBOL or the fourth-generation programming language Natural, toreside on network file servers and therefore be available todiverse users.andP;  Entire should support the Unix, VMS, MVS, VS andOS/2 operating systems and provide access to the DB2 and Adabasdata base management systems as well as any-to-any connectivity.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Software AG of North America Inc. (product development).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentOpen SystemsApplications ProgrammingDistributed Processing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>